141
00:29:58,775 --> 00:30:00,618
All his disciples went to pay homage.

142
00:30:00,819 --> 00:30:04,748
They all came excepting one monk whose absence was conspicuous.

143
00:30:04,980 --> 00:30:08,906
When the Buddha asked where Dhamma Rama was, they sent a monk to fetch him.

144
00:30:09,448 --> 00:30:13,714
And when he came, Buddha said to Dhamma Rama, these monks said that you had not come.

145
00:30:14,194 --> 00:30:16,679
Dhamma Rama replied, O Bhante, it is true.

146
00:30:17,039 --> 00:30:17,760
I did not come.

147
00:30:18,241 --> 00:30:25,853
I thought that if I sit down in my kundi and meditate and achieve some mental attainment, it would be the best way to pay homage to my teacher.

148
00:30:26,253 --> 00:30:28,136
So that is why I did not come.

149
00:30:28,116 --> 00:30:33,326
The Buddha said, Sadhu, Sadhu, Sadhu, all follow Dhamma Ram.

150
00:30:33,346 --> 00:30:35,871
From this we can see the place he gave to meditation.

151
00:30:36,310 --> 00:30:39,016
It really is the heart of Buddhist practice.

